      ],
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "fromDevice",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The capture device that represents the source camera. If you pass a "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "nil"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " value for this argument, an "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsinvalidargumentexception"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is generated."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "toDevice",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The capture device that represents the destination camera. If you pass a "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "nil"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " value for this argument, an "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsinvalidargumentexception"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is generated."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsdata"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " containing a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/simd/matrix_float4x3"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " matrix, which is a column major with 3 rows and 4 columns."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The extrinsic matrix consists of a unitless 3x3 rotation matrix (R) on the left and a translation (t) 3x1 column vector on the right, whose units are millimeters. The matrix expresses the destination camera’s extrinsics relative to the source camera. If "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "X_from"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is a 3D point in the source camera’s coordinate system, you project it into the destination camera’s coordinate system with "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "X_to = [R | t] * X_from"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Only physical cameras for which factory calibrations exist provide an extrinsic matrix. Virtual device cameras return "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "nil"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "If you enable video stabilization by setting a "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureconnection/1620484-preferredvideostabilizationmode"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " value, the pixels in stablized video frames no longer match the relative extrinsic matrix from one device to another due to warping. Disable video stabilization if you’re using the extrinsic matrix and camera intrinsics."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
